




HERE ARE A FEW INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE COPING OF DOLLY REED, MISS MAY
1966.
     THREE RIBBONS WILL BE NEEDED.  THE COLOR OF THE RIBBONS ARE
BLACK FOR THE FIRST RUNS, PURPLE FOR THE SECOND RUNS, AND
RED FOR THE THIRD RUNS.
     MISS REED IS IN TWO PARTS, THE FIRST BEING THE LONGEST.
EACH PART HAS THREE PASSES,  ONE FOR EACH OF THE COLORS.
     YOU MAY WISH TO CHANGE THE COLOR OF THE HAIR TO BROWN, IN
THAT CASE YOU SHOULD SUB THE BLACK RIBBON WITH A BROWN RIBBON. ALSO YOU
MAY WISH TO CHANGE MISS REEDS SWEATER, YOU CAN DO THIS BY CHANGING
THE PURPLE RIBBON TO A BLUE OR GREEN OR FOR THAT MATTER,  A BLACK IF
YOU USE BROWN FOR HER HAIR.  THE RED RIBBON SHOULD NOT BE SUBSTITUED
AS THIS RIBBON IS USED FOR BODY TONES.
     NOW, FOR THE LINE UP INSTRUCTIONS.  ALL SPROKET FEED PRINTER OWN
ERS, THIS IS YOUR DAY. WE USED A SPROKET FEED PRINTER FOR THE CREATION
OF MISS REED AND IT CERTAINALLY MAKES A DIFFERENCE.
     THERE ARE 8 SYNC LINES BEFORE EACH PART AND TO GET BEST COPY, WE
HAVE ARRANGED THEM SO THEY SHOULD TYPE OVER EACH OTHER AT THE START
OF EACH RUN... MAKE SURE YOUR PAPER IS STRAIGHT, AS IT CERTAINALLY NEEDS
BE.  YOU MAY WANT TO TAKE A PEN AND LINE UP THE LEFT EDGE OF THE PAPER
WHERE IT MEETS THE PLATEN. EACH SYNC LINE STARTS OUT WITH THE HEADER 
SYNC LINE AND THEN IT'S NUMBER  EXAMPLE;
SYNC LINE ONE
M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M

BY STOPPING THE TD AT THE FIRST AND LAST OF EACH SYNC LINE TO MAKE
ADJUSTMENTS YOU CAN ATTAIN GOOD ALIGNMENT BY THE EIGHTH SYNC LINE
EASILY.  DO TI WHEN YOU HAVE PLENTY OF TIME SO NOT TO RUSH THE JOB!
   I HAVE FOUND THAT HOLDING THE PAPER FROM THE
FRONT AND THE REAR AND PULLING IT TIGHT TOWARDS THE BACK OF THE MACHINE
YOU CAN MINIMUNIZE SLIPPING.  AFTER YOU ARE PRETTY WELL IN LINE, YOU 
MAY WANT TO TOUCH UP YOUR ALIGNMENT. THIS MAY BE DONE BY PULLING
THE PAPER SLIGHTLY AND NOT RETRACTING THE PRESSURE ROLLER.
     ONE MORE THING IF YOU HAVE ANY EMPTY TAPE ( RIBBONS ) SPOOLS,
IT IS A LOT EASIER IF YOU PRE-LOAD THE NEXT TAPE ( RIBBON ) AND HAVE IT
READY TO GO WHEN THE NEXT PASS COMES. 

     WELL, HAVE FUN, AND AWAY WE GO.






SYNC LINE 1
M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M M
